        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> any place(s) where we can apply this already?\r\n\r\nI looked into the default color scheme and with the semantics I had in mind `Conceal`, `NonText`, `LineNr`, and `SignColumn` would be good candidates (they all already have the same hl defined).\r\n\r\nHowever, in the default color scheme `Comment` is a different color than these, so if we link them to `Dimmed`, we need to set `Dimmed` to a specific color instead of linking it to `Comment`, because their hl is different (hope I'm explaining this clearly enough).\r\n\r\nI think introducing a new base hl group with a specific color instead of a link could be considered a breaking change maybe? Color schemes that don't define those four groups would get the new default color, but maybe this is not a big deal, they haven't defined them so they accept getting the default.\r\n\r\nCurrent patch (colors for light mode):\r\n```\r\nComment    guifg=NvimDarkGrey4\r\n\r\nDimmed     link=Comment\r\nConceal    guifg=NvimLightGrey4\r\nNonText    guifg=NvimLightGrey4\r\nLineNr     guifg=NvimLightGrey4\r\nSignColumn guifg=NvimLightGrey4\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n```\r\nComment    guifg=NvimDarkGrey4\r\n\r\nDimmed     guifg=NvimLightGrey4\r\nConceal    link=Dimmed\r\nNonText    link=Dimmed\r\nLineNr     link=Dimmed\r\nSignColumn link=Dimmed\r\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-05-01T15:54:52Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39505#issuecomment-4360185667",
            "id": 4360185667,
